      <entry xml:id="entry_mæstæg" xml:lang="os-x-iron" abv:completeness="english-questions">
        <form type="lemma"><orth>mæstæg</orth></form>
        <usg><lang/></usg>
        <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
            <q>плотный</q>
          </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
            <q>dense</q>
          </abv:tr></sense>
        <sense><note xml:lang="ru" type="comment">также </note><note xml:lang="en" type="comment"
            >also </note><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
            <q>пропитанный влагой</q>
            <note xml:lang="ru" type="comment"> (?)</note>
            <note xml:lang="en" type="comment"> (?)</note>
          </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
            <q>thick with moisture</q>
            <note type="comment"> (?)</note>
          </abv:tr><note xml:lang="ru" type="comment"> (мало употр.)</note><note xml:lang="en"
            type="comment"> (seldom used)</note></sense>
        <re>
          <form type="lemma"><orth><oRef>mæstæg</oRef> qæd</orth></form>
          <sense><tr xmlns="http://ossetic-studies.org/ns/abaevdict" xml:lang="ru">
              <q xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">плотная древесина</q>
            </tr><tr xmlns="http://ossetic-studies.org/ns/abaevdict" xml:lang="en">
              <q xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">dense timber</q>
            </tr></sense>
        </re>
        <exampleGrp xmlns="http://ossetic-studies.org/ns/abaevdict">
          <example>
            <quote xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">mæ ūdy nyxsyst, <oRef>nymmæstæg īs</oRef> dæ
              warzt</quote>
            <tr xml:lang="ru">
              <q xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">в моей душе закалилась, окрепла (<q>стала
                  плотной</q>) любовь к тебе</q>
            </tr>
            <tr xml:lang="en">
              <q xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">in my soul my love for you became tempered,
                grew strong (<q>became dense</q>)</q>
            </tr>
            <bibl xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><ref type="bibl" target="#src_F."/>
              <biblScope>VIII 36</biblScope></bibl>
          </example>
        </exampleGrp>
        <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w type="rec">masta-ka-</w><note
              xml:lang="ru" type="comment">, где <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w type="rec">masta-</w>
                <note xml:lang="ru" type="comment">из <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w type="rec"
                      >mad-ta</w>
                    <note xml:lang="ru" type="comment">от <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w type="rec"
                          >mad-</w>
                        <gloss><q>откармливать</q></gloss>, <gloss><q>делать полным, жирным,
                            плотным</q></gloss></mentioned></note></mentioned></note></mentioned></note></mentioned>;
          соответствия в других языках служат названиями <q rendition="#rend_doublequotes"
            >сгущенных</q> молочных продуктов, жира и пр.: <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/>
            <w>mastag</w>
            <gloss><q>творог</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal" extralang="fa"><lang/>
            <w>māst</w>
            <gloss><q>кислое молоко</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
            <w>māsta-</w>
            <gloss><q>сгущенное молоко</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="inc-x-old"><lang/>
            <w>mastu-</w>
            <gloss><q>кислые сливки</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
            <w>μεστός</w>
            <gloss><q>полный</q></gloss>, <gloss><q>наполненный</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="grc"><w>μαστός</w>
            <gloss><q>mamma</q></gloss></mentioned>. От основы <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w
              type="rec">mazda-</w>
              (<?oxy_comment_start author="oleg" timestamp="20220624T130338+0300" comment="Iranian or IE?"?><w
              type="rec">ṃzdo-</w><?oxy_comment_end?>)</mentioned> производят <mentioned
            xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
            <w>mastāña-</w>
            <gloss><q>корм</q></gloss>
            <note type="bibl">(<bibl><author>Bailey</author>, <ref type="bibl" target="#ref_BSOAS"/>
                <biblScope>1956 XVIII 33 сл.</biblScope></bibl>)</note></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
            <w>azdya-</w>
            <note xml:lang="ru" type="comment">(← <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w type="rec"
                >ṃzdyo</w></mentioned>)</note>
            <gloss><q>откормленный</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="inc-x-old"><lang/>
            <w>medas-</w>
            <gloss><q>жир</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/>
            <w>Mast</w>
            <gloss><q>откармливание</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><w>mast</w>
            <gloss><q>откормленный</q></gloss>, <gloss><q>жирный</q></gloss></mentioned>. Ср. далее
          от того же корня <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w type="rec">mad-</w></mentioned>
          <mentioned xml:lang="bgp"><lang/>
            <w>maδaɣ</w>
            <gloss><q>свертываться</q></gloss>, <gloss><q>густеть</q></gloss>,
                <gloss><q>замерзать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="bgn"><lang/>
            <w>madag</w>
            <gloss><q>сгущенное молоко</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
            <w>māsīdan</w>
            <gloss><q>створаживаться</q></gloss>, <gloss><q>свертываться</q></gloss>,
                <gloss><q>густеть</q></gloss>, <gloss><q>замерзать</q></gloss></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
            <w>matar</w>, <w>matra</w>
            <gloss><q>створоженное молоко</q></gloss></mentioned>. <mentioned xml:lang="hu"><lang/>
            <w>vastag</w>
            <gloss><q>плотный</q></gloss></mentioned> идет, возможно, из иранского. Другая
          семантическая линия — в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_mast"><w>mast</w>
            <gloss><q>горький</q></gloss></ref>?</etym>
        <etym xml:lang="en">Goes back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w type="rec">masta-ka-</w><note
              xml:lang="en" type="comment">, where <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w type="rec"
                  >masta-</w>
                <note xml:lang="en" type="comment">from <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w type="rec"
                      >mad-ta</w>
                    <note xml:lang="en" type="comment"
                      >from <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w type="rec">mad-</w>
                        <gloss><q>fatten</q></gloss>, <gloss><q>make dense,
                        full</q></gloss></mentioned></note></mentioned></note></mentioned></note></mentioned>;
          correspondences in other languages serve as names of <q rendition="#rend_doublequotes"
            >condensed</q> dairy products, fat etc.: <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/>
            <w>mastag</w>
            <gloss><q><?oxy_comment_start author="oleg" timestamp="20220624T131846+0300" comment="Abaev has творог (quark?), but Balochi online dictionary gives meaning &quot;yoghurt&quot;"?>yoghurt<?oxy_comment_end?></q></gloss></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="pal" extralang="fa"><lang/>
            <w>māst</w>
            <gloss><q>sour milk</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
            <w>māsta-</w>
            <gloss><q>condensed milk</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="inc-x-old"><lang/>
            <w>mastu-</w>
            <gloss><q>sour cream</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
            <w>μεστός</w>
            <gloss><q>full</q></gloss>, <gloss><q>filled</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="grc"><w>μαστός</w>
            <gloss><q><foreign>mamma</foreign></q></gloss></mentioned>. From the stem <mentioned
            xml:lang="ira"><w type="rec">mazda-</w>
              (<?oxy_comment_start author="oleg" timestamp="20220624T130338+0300" comment="Iranian or IE?"?><w
              type="rec">ṃzdo-</w><?oxy_comment_end?>)</mentioned> are derived <mentioned
            xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
            <w>mastāña-</w>
            <gloss><q>forage</q></gloss>
            <note type="bibl">(<bibl><author>Bailey</author>, <ref type="bibl" target="#ref_BSOAS"/>
                <biblScope>1956 XVIII 33 ff.</biblScope></bibl>)</note></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
            <w>azdya-</w>
            <note xml:lang="en" type="comment">(← <mentioned
                xml:lang="ira"><w type="rec">ṃzdyo</w></mentioned>)</note>
            <gloss><q>fattened</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="inc-x-old"><lang/>
            <w>medas-</w>
            <gloss><q>the fat</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/>
            <w>Mast</w>
            <gloss><q>fattening</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><w>mast</w>
            <gloss><q>fattened</q></gloss>, <gloss><q>fatty</q></gloss></mentioned>. Cf. further
          from the same root <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w type="rec">mad-</w></mentioned>
          <mentioned xml:lang="bgp"><lang/>
            <w>maδaɣ</w>
            <gloss><q>to curdle</q></gloss>, <gloss><q>thicken (intr.)</q></gloss>, <gloss><q>freeze
                (intr.)</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="bgn"><lang/>
            <w>madag</w>
            <gloss><q>condensed milk</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
            <w>māsīdan</w>
            <gloss><q>clot</q></gloss>, <gloss><q>curdle</q></gloss>, <gloss><q>thicken
              (intr.)</q></gloss>, <gloss><q>freeze (intr.)</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
            <w>matar</w>, <w>matra</w>
            <gloss><q>curdled milk</q></gloss></mentioned>. <mentioned xml:lang="hu"><lang/>
            <w>vastag</w>
            <gloss><q>dense</q></gloss></mentioned> possibly comes from Iranian. Is another semantic
          lineage found in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_mast"><w>mast</w>
            <gloss><q>sour</q></gloss></ref>?</etym>
      </entry>
